7 An Act relating to poor persons; amending 56 O.S.
2021, Section 4002.12, as last amended by Section 7,
8 Chapter 448, O.S.L. 2024 (56 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
4002.12), which relates to minimum rates of
9 reimbursement; extending deadlines; and providing an
effective date.
10
11
12 AMENDMENT NO. 1. Page 1, strike the title, enacting clause and
entire bill and insert
13
14 “An Act relating to the state Medicaid program;
amending 56 O.S. 2021, Section 4002.12, as last
15 amended by Section 7, Chapter 448, O.S.L. 2024 (56
O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 4002.12), which relates to
16 minimum rates of reimbursement; extending certain
termination dates; establishing certain reimbursement
17 rates for multistate contracts; authorizing
promulgation of certain rules; defining terms; and
18 providing an effective date.
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 56 O.S. 2021, Section 4002.12, as
21 last amended by Section 7, Chapter 448, O.S.L. 2024 (56 O.S. Supp.
22 2025, Section 4002.12), is amended to read as follows:
23 Section 4002.12. A. Until July 1, 2027 July 1, 2028, the
24 Oklahoma Health Care Authority shall establish minimum rates of
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3650 Page 1

1 reim bursement from contracted entities to providers who elect not to
2 enter into value-based payment arrangements under subsection B of
3 this section or other alternative payment agreements for health care
4 items and services furnished by such providers to enrollees of the
5 state Medicaid program. Except as provided by subsection I of this
6 section, until July 1, 2027 July 1, 2028, such reimbursement rates
7 shall be equal to or greater than:
8 1. For an item or service provided by a participating provider
9 who is in the network of the contracted entity, one hundred percent
10 (100%) of the reimbursement rate for the applicable service in the
11 applicable fee schedule of the Authority; or
12 2. For an item or service provided by a non-participating
13 provider or a provider who is not in the network of the contracted
14 entity, ninety percent (90%) of the reimbursement rate for the
15 applicable service in the applicable fee schedule of the Authority
16 as of January 1, 2021.
17 B. A contracted entity shall offer value-based payment
18 arrangements to all providers in its network capable of entering
19 into value-based payment arrangements. Such arrangements shall be
20 optional for the provider but shall be tied to reimbursement
21 incentives when quality metrics are met. The quality measures used
22 by a contracted entity to determine reimbursement amounts to
23 providers in value-based payment arrangements shall align with the
24 quality measures of the Authority for contracted entities.
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3650 Page 2

1 C. Notwithstanding any other provision of this section, the
2 Authority shall comply with payment methodologies required by
3 federal law or regulation for specific types of providers including,
4 but not limited to, Federally Qualified Health Centers, rural health
5 clinics, pharmacies, Indian Health Care Providers and emergency
6 services.
7 D. A contracted entity shall offer all rural health clinics
8 (RHCs) contracts that reimburse RHCs using the methodology in place
9 for each specific RHC prior to January 1, 2023, including any and
10 all annual rate updates. The contracted entity shall comply with
11 all federal program rules and requirements, and the transformed
12 Medicaid delivery system shall not interfere with the program as
13 designed.
14 E. The Oklahoma Health Care Authority shall establish minimum
15 rates of reimbursement from contracted entities to Certified
16 Community Behavioral Health Clinic (CCBHC) providers who elect
17 alternative payment arrangements equal to the prospective payment
18 system rate under the Medicaid State Plan.
19 F. The Authority shall establish an incentive payment under the
20 Supplemental Hospital Offset Payment Program that is determined by
21 value-based outcomes for providers other than hospitals.
22 G. Psychologist reimbursement shall reflect outcomes.
23 Reimbursement shall not be limited to therapy and shall include but
24 not be limited to testing and assessment.
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3650 Page 3

1 H. Coverage for Medicaid ground transportation services by
2 licensed Oklahoma emergency medical services shall be reimbursed at
3 no less than the published Medicaid rates as set by the Authority.
4 All currently published Medicaid Healthcare Common Procedure Coding
5 System (HCPCS) codes paid by the Authority shall continue to be paid
6 by the contracted entity. The contracted entity shall comply with
7 all reimbursement policies established by the Authority for the
8 ambulance providers. Contracted entities shall accept the modifiers
9 established by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services
10 currently in use by Medicare at the time of the transport of a
11 member that is dually eligible for Medicare and Medicaid.
12 I. 1. The rate paid to participating pharmacy providers is
13 independent of subsection A of this section and shall be the same as
14 the fee-for-service rate employed by the Authority for the Medicaid
15 program as stated in the payment methodology in OAC 317:30-5-78,
16 unless the participating pharmacy provider elects to enter into
17 other alternative payment agreements.
18 2. A pharmacy or pharmacist shall receive direct payment or
19 reimbursement from the Authority or contracted entity when providing
20 a health care service to the Medicaid member at a rate no less than
21 that of other health care providers for providing the same service.
22 J. Notwithstanding any other provision of this section,
23 anesthesia shall continue to be reimbursed equal to or greater than
24 the anesthesia fee schedule established by the Authority as of
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3650 Page 4

1 Janu ary 1, 2021. Anesthesia providers may also enter into value-
2 based payment arrangements under this section or alternative payment
3 arrangements for services furnished to Medicaid members.
4 K. The Authority shall specify in the requests for proposals a
5 reasonable time frame in which a contracted entity shall have
6 entered into a certain percentage, as determined by the Authority,
7 of value-based contracts with providers.
8 L. Capitation rates established by the Oklahoma Health Care
9 Authority and paid to contracted entities under capitated contracts
10 shall be updated annually and in accordance with 42 C.F.R., Section
11 438.3. Capitation rates shall be approved as actuarially sound as
12 determined by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services in
13 accordance with 42 C.F.R., Section 438.4 and the following:
14 1. Actuarial calculations must include utilization and
15 expenditure assumptions consistent with industry and local
16 standards; and
17 2. Capitation rates shall be risk-adjusted and shall include a
18 portion that is at risk for achievement of quality and outcomes
19 measures.
20 M. The Authority may establish a symmetric risk corridor for
21 contracted entities.
22 N. The Authority shall establish a process for annual recovery
23 of funds from, or assessment of penalties on, contracted entities
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3650 Page 5

1 that do not meet the medical loss ratio standards stipulated in
2 Section 4002.5 of this title.
3 O. 1. The Authority shall, through the financial reporting
4 required under subsection G of Section 4002.12b of this title,
5 determine the percentage of health care expenses by each contracted
6 entity on primary care services.
7 2. Not later than the end of the fourth year of the initial
8 contracting period, each contracted entity shall be currently
9 spending not less than eleven percent (11%) of its total health care
10 expenses on primary care services.
11 3. The Authority shall monitor the primary care spending of
12 each contracted entity and require each contracted entity to
13 maintain the level of spending on primary care services stipulated
14 in paragraph 2 of this subsection.
15 P. 1. Notwithstanding the provisions of subsection A of this
16 section but subject to all other provisions of this section, for an
17 item or service delivered under a multistate contract, the
18 reimbursement rate for that item or service shall be the lesser of:
19 a. the rate specified in the multistate contract, or
20 b. the applicable rate in the fee schedule of the
21 Authority.
22 2. The Oklahoma Health Care Authority Board may promulgate
23 rules to implement the provisions of this section including, but not
24 limited to, rules that further define the terms used in this
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 3650 Page 6

1 subs ection or that set limitations or restrictions around the
2 applicability of the provisions of this subsection.
3 3. As used in this subsection:
4 a. “multistate contract” means a contract that a
5 contracted entity or its parent company holds with
6 another entity under which the entity provides health
7 care services on behalf of the contracted entity
8 throughout a service area that includes this state and
9 at least one other state, and
10 b. “parent company” means any company that directly or
11 indirectly controls a contracted entity.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.”
13 Passed the Senate the 29th day of April, 2026.
